    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Religious movement originating from William Faw Faw (Waw-No-She) (c. 1854-1924), an Otoe-Missouria prophet; became popular amongst Native North Americans in Oklahoma in the late 19th century to the early 20th century. With a focus on returning back to Native lifeways, adherents would enact complex dances and ceremonies, as well as wearing heavily decorated regalia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
